$PROB template control stream ;----------------------------------------------------------------------- ; Project: Investigating the contribution of residual unexplained ; variability in nonlinear mixed-effect approach ; Model: Two-compartment model with linear elimination ; Estim: First-order conditional est. with interaction ; Author: Mutaz M. Jaber <jaber038@umn.edu> ; Date created: 9/7/2021 ; Date modified: 9/7/2021 ;----------------------------------------------------------------------- $INPUT ID TIME DV AMT MDV EVID $DATA ../../../../data/spa1/S2/dat80.csv ignore=@ $SUBR ADVAN4 TRANS4 $EST MET=1 NOABORT MAX=10000 PRINT=5 INTER NSIG=2 $PK ET1 = EXP(ETA(1)*THETA(6)) ET2 = EXP(ETA(2)*THETA(7)) ET3 = EXP(ETA(3)*THETA(8)) ET4 = EXP(ETA(4)*THETA(9)) ET5 = EXP(ETA(5)*THETA(10))
CL = 5.0 * THETA(1) * ET1 V2 = 35 * THETA(2) * ET2 Q = 50 * THETA(3) * ET3 V3 = 50 * THETA(4) * ET4 KA = 0.7 * THETA(5) * ET5 SC = V2 $ERROR CVERR = 0.05 W = THETA(11)*F*CVERR
Y = F + W*ERR(1)
$THETA (0,1) ; CL (0,1) ; V2 (0,1) ; Q (0,1) ; V3 (0,1) ; KA (0,1) ; IIVCL (0,1) ; IIVV2 (0,1) ; IIVQ (0,1) ; IIVV3 (0,1) ; IIVKA (0,1) ; CVPropErr
$OMEGA (0.09 FIX)x5 $SIGMA 1 FIX ; [P] $COVARIANCE UNCOND
